ID: 1104
Text:  The first premise and the conclusion are not properly translated as identity statements since the is in those statements is the is of predication rather than of identity.  Instead they should be translated using a predicate letter.  Using g to designate God and j to designate Jesus and the predicate letter E for the property of being eternal the first premise is Eg and the conclusion is Ej.     The second premise appears to contain an is of identity in which case it can be properly symbolized as j = g.  But your remark that Jesus is a subset of God suggests that strict identity is not desired here. If however the first premise means that all members making up the set God have the property of being eternal
